    • Constructor Detail

      • Puzzle

        public Puzzle(int n)
        A (n*n)-1 Puzzle constructor. It creates a N-Puzzle with game elements in [0, (n*n)-1], 0 being the blank space. If the user wants to generate a 15-Puzzle, the parameter passed to the constructor should be 4. This will guaranty that the puzzle created is always an (n*n-1)-Puzzle so it matches the general algorithms
        Parameters:
        n - The dimension of the puzzle grid. Should be > 1.

      • Puzzle

        public Puzzle(int[] array)
        Constructs a (n*n)-1 Puzzle from an array. Initialize a puzzle from an array of 16 elements in [0,(n*n)-1], 0 being the blank space. The dimension of the grid: n = sqrt(array.length).
        Parameters:
        array - A N-Puzzle in array representation.

    • Method Detail

      • getSize

        public int getSize()
        Size of the puzzle.
        Returns:
        The size of the puzzle. Total tiles, including the blank space.

      • getDimension

        public int getDimension()
        Dimension of the puzzle grid.
        Returns:
        The number of rows/columns in the puzzle equal to the square root of the size of the puzzle (the size of the puzzle includes the blank space). e.g. a 15-Puzzle has dimension 4.

      • toArray

        public int[] toArray()
        Array representation of the puzzle
        Returns:
        The array representation of the puzzle

      • shuffle

        public void shuffle()
        Shuffles the puzzle. It shuffles the puzzle making random movements of the blank space. The number of random movements is in the range of [10^(n-2), 10^(n-1)).

      • movePiece

        public Puzzle movePiece(int id)
        Swap a piece with the blank space. A piece can only be moved if it is adjacent to the blank space. This method clones the puzzle instance and move the piece in the new puzzle.
        Parameters:
        id - Piece id in [1,size]
        Returns:
        A new puzzle with the piece specified in the parameter swapped with the blank space. NULL if the piece can't be moved.

      • validMoves

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> validMoves()
        Computes the possible moves in the board.
        Returns:
        A list of integers representing the blank space neighbors. This list is never empty.

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Prints the puzzle board. Before printing, it verifies the invariant of the puzzle.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object

      • isSolvable

        public boolean isSolvable()
        Checks whether the puzzle is solvable or not. It calculates the number of inversions and verifies if the puzzle is solvable depending on the board dimension.
        Returns:
        Boolean indicating whether the puzzle solvable or not.
        See Also:
        The 8 puzzle problem

      • inversions

        public int inversions()
        Computes the number of inversions. An inversion is define for a pair of tiles a,b if a > b but b is after a in an array representation of the board. This method computes the number of inversions of the puzzle by adding the inversions of each tile.
        Returns:
        int with the number of inversions.

      • transpose

        public Puzzle transpose()
        Transpose the puzzle to the right. It creates a new puzzle with the rows and columns transposed from this.
        Returns:
        A new puzzle with this instance transposed to the right.

      • invariant

        public boolean invariant()
        Verifies the invariant of the puzzle. Checks on:
        • The grid and the array are equal
        • The values of tiles are from 0 to size-1
        • The array's length is equal to the grid's length equal to the size of puzzle
        • The zero coordinate is the current position of the blank space
        Returns:
        True if the state of the puzzle is correct.

      • isSolved

        Returns:
        True if the puzzle is already solved.
